<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Automated"><PMID Version="1">41224030</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2026</Year><Month>01</Month><Day>02</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>01</Month><Day>02</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print-Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1873-6971</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>188</Volume><PubDate><Year>2026</Year><Month>Jan</Month></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Fitoterapia</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Fitoterapia</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Chromone derivative with a spiro[chromene-5,2'-furan] ring and sesquiterpenoids from the marine algicolous Trichoderma asperellum Z54-7.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>106985</StartPage><MedlinePgn>106985</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1016/j.fitote.2025.106985</ELocationID><ELocationID EIdType="pii" ValidYN="Y">S0367-326X(25)00611-2</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>A novel chromone derivative with a unique carbon skeleton, trichochromone A (1), a new trichothecene sesquiterpenoid, trichodermarin O (2), and two new farnesane-type sesquiterpenoids, trichodersanins A and B (3 and 4), were isolated from the fungus Trichoderma asperellum Z54-7 obtained from the surface of marine red alga Hyalosiphonia caespitosa. Their structures and configurations were elucidated by detailed spectroscopic analysis and single-crystal X-ray diffraction. Trichochromone A (1) features a spiro[chromene-5,2'-furan] ring. Trichodermarin O (2) is the second trichothecene derivative with an aminosugar unit. Compounds 1 and 3/4 exhibited weak inhibition against one marine phytoplankton species, Chattonella marina.</AbstractText><CopyrightInformation>Copyright &#xa9; 2024. Published by Elsevier B.V.</CopyrightInformation></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Shi</LastName><ForeName>Zhen-Zhen</ForeName><Initials>ZZ</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affili